<HEAD>Minor Earthquake Shakes Tri-State Corner of Tenn., Ky. and Va.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRISTOL, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A minor earthquake shook cupboards Tuesday
near the three-state corner of Tennessee, Kentucky and Virginia,
but no injuries were reported, earthquake officials said.
   The quake, which occurred northwest of Bristol at 10:26 a.m.,
measured 3.2 on the Richter scale, said Jill Hart, with the Center
for Earthquake Research and Information at Memphis State
University. A quake of 3.5 magnitude can cause slight damage.
   The tri-state area is seismically active, although it's not
noted for having major earthquakes, Ms. Hart said. The exact center
of the quake was not yet located, she said.
