<HEAD>Dolly Parton Inducted Into Star Walk</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Country music star Dolly Parton
decorated a slab of wet coment along Star Walk on Tuesday with her
footprints, handprints and a small rhinestone butterfly.
   ``Several people asked me if I was going to leave the prints of
something else,'' the buxom blonde told about 200 people gathered
for the noon ceremonies.
   ``I said, `Heavens no!' I'm afraid some little kid might fall in
it and get killed,'' she said with a giggle.
   Star Walk, a year-old attraction at a new outdoor shopping
complex, honors country artists who have won Grammy awards.
   Miss Parton and the crew from her variety television show are in
Nashville this week to tape the season finale of ``Dolly.''
