<2ND_LINE>AM-Other Awards,0174</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>With AM-Oscar Nominations Bjt</HEAD>
<HEAD>Prestigious Oscar, the Motion Picture Grand-Daddy, Not the Only
Game in Town</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Winning an Academy Award is
considered the most prestigious honor bestowed by Hollywood, but
Oscar isn't the only game in town. Recognition is also given by
peers, critics and the public.
   If the industry grand-daddy given by the Academy of Motion
Picture Arts and Sciences eludes, moviemakers and stars still have
dozens of chances at lesser trophies.
   There are the Golden Globes, viewed as a barometer of Oscar
sentiment, and awards given by L.A. Film Critics, N.Y. Film
Critics, the People's Choice Awards, Writer's Guild Awards,
Director's Guild Awards, National Board of Review Awards, Orson
Welles Awards, Cable TV ACE Awards, Cinematographer's Awards,
Stuntmen Association Awards, Cannes Film Festival Awards, NAACP
Image Awards and Hispanic Film Awards.
   Notable animal performances are also recognized with the annual
Patsy Awards, and for those with a jaundiced view, there are the
Golden Raspberry Awards given for the worst in film.
</TEXT>
